Let's calculate each step by step.

1. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Total Liabilities are given by "Total Current Liabilities": 2,110,671.05  
• Total Owner’s Equity is: 14,103,190.60  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 2,110,671.05 / 14,103,190.60  
  ≈ 0.1497, which we round to 0.15  

2. Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit is: 1,103,190.60  
• Total Revenue is: 5,813,420.67  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (1,103,190.60 / 5,813,420.67) × 100%  
  ≈ 18.97%

3. Return on Assets (ROA)  
• Total Assets (ending) is: 16,213,861.65  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%  
  = (1,103,190.60 / 16,213,861.65) × 100%  
  ≈ 6.80%

4. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Accounts Receivable at the end is 1,355,463.34; the beginning balance is 0. Hence, average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 1,355,463.34)/2 = 677,731.67  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 5,813,420.67 / 677,731.67  
  ≈ 8.58  

Thus, the final answer in JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.15", "Net Profit Margin": "18.97%", "Return on Assets (ROA)": "6.80%", "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "8.58"}}
